# Homelab SSH host CA. Every managed host serves a step-ca-signed host
# certificate (ssh_host_cert role); this one @cert-authority line is
# what replaces the per-host pinned keys that used to live in this
# directory. The `*` pattern is intentional — scoping is enforced by
# the certificate's own principals, not by the hostname pattern.
# See AnsibleSpecs slices/ssh-host-ca.md.
@cert-authority * ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIPr0uj0iU/LAoFwB9HUmFiPC+5qsXdPRVHFn6nIf9EPm homelab-ssh-host-ca
